   "source": [
    "# Gaussian chain segmental distribution\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 56,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from scipy.sparse import diags\n",
    "from scipy.sparse.linalg import eigsh\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "%config InlineBackend.figure_format = 'retina'\n",
    "\n",
    "# default values for plotting\n",
    "plt.rcParams.update({'font.size': 12,\n",
    "                     'axes.titlesize': 18,\n",

    "                     'axes.labelpad': 14,\n",
    "                     'lines.linewidth': 1,\n",
    "                     'lines.markersize': 10,\n",
    "                     'xtick.labelsize' : 16,\n",

    "                     'xtick.top' : True,\n",

   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "R=1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [

     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "4*np.pi*(1.1e-6)**3/3/(4*np.pi*(0.75e-6)**3/3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "epsi=np.linspace(0,1,20)\n",
    "x=(3*epsi**2-3*epsi+1)\n",
    "y=(3*epsi**2-3*epsi+1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "outputs": [

   "source": [
    "#plt.plot(epsi,x)\n",
    "plt.plot(x,1/y,'.')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('variance')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('amplitude')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Unperturbed Gaussian Chain"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "r=np.linspace(-2,2,1000)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "R=1\n",
    "f = lambda x,r: np.exp(-2*r**2/(2*R**2*(3*x**2-3*x+1)))/(3*x**2-3*x+1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dens=[]\n",
    "for p in r:\n",
    "    y, err = integrate.quad(f, 0, 1, args=(p,))\n",
    "    dens.append(y)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x7f90948b6490>]"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 12,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.semilogy(r,dens)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from scipy.optimize import curve_fit"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def gfit(x,*args):\n",
    "    amp = args\n",
    "    n=50\n",
    "    var_range=np.linspace(0.3,1,n)\n",
    "    y=0\n",
    "    for i,var in enumerate(var_range):\n",
    "        y=y+amp[i]*np.exp(-x**2/(2*R**2*var))/var\n",
    "    return(y)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "n=50\n",
    "var_range=np.linspace(0.3,1,n)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "params = 1/np.linspace(0.3,1,n)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "fitted_params,_ = curve_fit(gfit,r, np.array(dens), p0=params)\n"
   ]
  },
